					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">qbradq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Personally I do not like doing this within a game mode. It's true, my sprite generator never runs at the same time as my object updates, but this type of data interleaving over-complicates your code. Only if I were <em>very</em> desperate for RAM would this be an option for me.</div>
<br />I wouldn't be able to make my game without this. The main engine uses every last byte of RAM, so I can't afford to have memory allocated for a bunch of stuff that just isn't running during gameplay (title screen, menus, bonus stages, etc). The main systems, like the ones dealing with music, sprites, etc. use global variables, because those are used by all program modes. It's not a difficult thing to manage at all: whatever is used by multiple program modes is global.</div>

